<h1 id="third-party-projects">
<a class="heading-anchor" href="#third-party-projects" hidden><svg width="16" height="16"><use xlink:href="https://thisweek.gnome.org/images/icons.svg#anchor"></use></svg></a>Third Party Projects
</h1>

<h3 id="tagger">
<a class="heading-anchor" href="#tagger" hidden><svg width="16" height="16"><use xlink:href="https://thisweek.gnome.org/images/icons.svg#anchor"></use></svg></a>Tagger <a href="https://flathub.org/apps/details/org.nickvision.tagger"><svg width='16' height='16'><use xlink:href='https://thisweek.gnome.org/images/icons.svg#link'></use></svg></a>
</h3><p>Tag your music.</p>
<p><a href="https://matrix.to/#/@nlogozzo:matrix.org">Nick</a> says</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Tagger is now at <a href="https://github.com/NickvisionApps/Tagger/releases/tag/2023.7.1-beta2">V2023.7.1-beta2</a> !
V2023.7.1 is shaping up to be a huge release with new features, more customization options, better performance, many bug fixes, and an improved user interface.</p>
<p>Here&rsquo;s the full changelog so far:</p>
<ul>
<li>Added support for the following tag properties: BPM, Composer, Description, Publisher, ISRC</li>
<li>Added help documentation with yelp-tools, accessible from the Help menu action</li>
<li>Added more file sorting options</li>
<li>Improved album art design and added support for managing back cover art and exporting album art</li>
<li>Fixed an issue where corrupted music files would crash the app. Tagger will now display a dialog to warn the user of corrupted files</li>
<li>Improved UI</li>
<li>Updated translations (Thanks everyone on Weblate!)

<img src="https://thisweek.gnome.org/posts/2023/07/twig-104/sWyycQKmKJrZHVPhTnHttFyc.png" alt="" />
</li>
</ul>
</blockquote>


<h3 id="parabolic">
<a class="heading-anchor" href="#parabolic" hidden><svg width="16" height="16"><use xlink:href="https://thisweek.gnome.org/images/icons.svg#anchor"></use></svg></a>Parabolic <a href="https://flathub.org/apps/details/org.nickvision.tubeconverter"><svg width='16' height='16'><use xlink:href='https://thisweek.gnome.org/images/icons.svg#link'></use></svg></a>
